Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.88,0:00:04.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, we're going to discuss what is real success.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.42,0:00:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Real?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.98,0:00:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Real.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.82,0:00:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's the topic.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.08,0:00:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what would you say, when I think of that, what is real success,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.10,0:00:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,immediately people think that money and position and personal goals are what they consider is real success.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.78,0:00:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,When I ask you as a spiritual teacher what real success is, how would you interpret that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.40,0:00:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I would, as a spiritual teacher, say it has to do with fulfilling your obligations to experience the presence of God to the fullest possible extent.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.52,0:01:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And to begin to realize that as you do this, everything reveals itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.07,0:01:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,As divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.22,0:01:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,As you ask me the question, the divinity of this moment is now revealing itself to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.92,0:01:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems at first like an artificially posed thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.09,0:01:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you realize that there is no such thing as an artificially posed thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.92,0:01:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That thought is originating from the presence of God as the reality of you and I sitting here on this couch speaking at this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.81,0:01:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the presence of God as existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.52,0:01:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,From moment to moment, the existence of that which is real is nothing but the realization that God is the essence of all reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.92,0:01:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Lord. Amen.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.02,0:01:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,God told me to say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.58,0:02:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you know, a lot of people think that they're successful if they have money.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.56,0:02:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.62,0:02:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of them, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.44,0:02:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So you've always said that if a person, as far as it goes, is if they do the best they can at what they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.92,0:02:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.78,0:02:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That success will automatically come to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.46,0:02:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.73,0:02:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't want to put down material success.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.17,0:02:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay to be a millionaire and to be world famous and on television every day and have worshipful crowds.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.31,0:02:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.47,0:02:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point to make that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.73,0:02:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.67,0:02:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how success comes to that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.36,0:02:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We need famous people to hang out around and enjoy their presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.92,0:02:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So we get to share in the joy of their success.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.74,0:03:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So if people are joyfully successful, I say thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.97,0:03:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your success because we're all enjoying your enjoyment of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.18,0:03:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And we all need Bob.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.01,0:03:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Bob Hope and Bing Crosby.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.74,0:03:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That sort of dates me, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.80,0:03:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Who would be a current example?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.60,0:03:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, a lot of people, you know, they...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.82,0:03:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you give me a current example?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.98,0:03:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, like, you know, fame.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.40,0:03:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, they want to be famous and recognized.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.96,0:03:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I were.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.14,0:03:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there any people like that today?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.76,0:03:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.64,0:03:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,People.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.18,0:03:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is these people?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.92,0:03:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you name me one successful person?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.64,0:03:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, many come to mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.60,0:03:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.08,0:03:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Like?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.64,0:03:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Jay Letterman.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.44,0:03:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.78,0:03:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Jay Letterman.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.44,0:03:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Jay Leno.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.54,0:03:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, oh, oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.66,0:03:51.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I see what you're saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.14,0:03:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know who they are, but it sounds good to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.30,0:04:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.12,0:04:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you know, politicians are, you know, famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.12,0:04:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,President.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.88,0:04:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.42,0:04:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is the president of the United States?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.10,0:04:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Obama.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.38,0:04:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Michelle Obama?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.62,0:04:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.62,0:04:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Barack.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.24,0:04:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Barack?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.68,0:04:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Barack.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.92,0:04:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Barack Obama.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.95,0:04:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a funny name.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.05,0:04:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that his real first name?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.35,0:04:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Barack?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.01,0:04:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.41,0:04:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Barack.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.45,0:04:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.02,0:04:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, he seemed like a nice fellow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.36,0:04:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I liked him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.30,0:04:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And with the name of Barack, if Obama would become president, you really got to have something
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.48,0:04:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,on the ball.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.26,0:04:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.28,0:04:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It was John Obama.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.06,0:04:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Phil.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.90,0:04:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, my question is, real success, is it what you are in the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.16,0:04:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Or is it how the world sees you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.21,0:05:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the real success is its own self-fulfillment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.29,0:05:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Real success is achieving the fulfillment and expression of your own potentialities.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.12,0:05:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The world may or may not recognize that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.65,0:05:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the world's response to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.04,0:05:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,However, real success would really include not only fulfillment of your own potentiality,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.34,0:05:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but the response of the world to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.52,0:05:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's perfectly all right to be president of the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.80,0:05:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's great that he fulfilled his potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.79,0:05:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And I also enjoy the fact that the world recognizes it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.04,0:05:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a name, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.28,0:05:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.70,0:05:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Philip Obama?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.64,0:05:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.88,0:05:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Barack.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.72,0:05:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Barack Obama?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.78,0:05:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.34,0:05:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's his first name?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.40,0:05:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.54,0:05:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Barack?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.96,0:05:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.60,0:05:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.83,0:05:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I enjoy him when I see him speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.05,0:06:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I think he's very eloquent.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.71,0:06:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Very eloquent speaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.94,0:06:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.09,0:06:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,More eloquent than I am, he's very eloquent.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.80,0:06:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.98,0:06:15.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad he's president because he's very eloquent and sort of elegant, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.22,0:06:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Very elegant, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.50,0:06:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, but who you are in the world versus what you are in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.48,0:06:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, how would you describe that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.41,0:06:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, who is the personality?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.27,0:06:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And what?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.51,0:06:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It has to do with function.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.42,0:06:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a what when you sit here and talk to the camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.50,0:06:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.12,0:06:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, I'm being a what.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.20,0:06:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is a who being that what.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.00,0:06:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.66,0:06:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there's both a who and a what.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.12,0:06:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And the what is the momentary expression of that who.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.34,0:07:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is being whatever that person is being at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.26,0:07:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.22,0:07:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.02,0:07:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.10,0:07:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay to be both who and what.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.48,0:07:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.86,0:07:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, you really have to be both a who and a what at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.22,0:07:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Because who is it that's being a what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.40,0:07:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, do you think that the ego comes in to play when the who is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.73,0:07:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I think the who, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.43,0:07:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The who is the...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.89,0:07:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Inter...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.47,0:07:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the villain, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.93,0:07:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The who.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.51,0:07:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.27,0:07:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And the what is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.77,0:07:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the external expression of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.95,0:07:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, everybody is both who and what at the same time, all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.13,0:07:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If you think about who, then you get sort of expanded.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.94,0:07:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Or you get embarrassed or nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.10,0:07:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know who's speaking right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.54,0:08:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I guess me, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.20,0:08:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But what is it that's speaking?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.98,0:08:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Because whatever is speaking right now is happening spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.14,0:08:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.74,0:08:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have time to give thought to what I'm going to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.36,0:08:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.00,0:08:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And you don't give me any time to say or to think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.23,0:08:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What's it all about, baby?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.99,0:08:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Is real success how people see you or how you see yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.04,0:08:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, real success, I think, fulfills both.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.23,0:08:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be really successful and keep it privately to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.99,0:08:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's real success.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.19,0:08:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You fulfill your own goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.19,0:08:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need public rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.27,0:08:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need recognition.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.04,0:08:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If my goal is to chop down this tree and have it all sawed up by 4 o'clock this afternoon,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.37,0:08:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,then when I do that, I'm a real success.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.17,0:08:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.91,0:09:02.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And nobody knows about it except myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.25,0:09:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, real success to me is then the self-fulfillment of a self-goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.68,0:09:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And the world may or may not even notice it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.20,0:09:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.84,0:09:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I have to make myself happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.91,0:09:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we're talking...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.67,0:09:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm talking this morning, and I have to make myself happy that I'm understanding the points that you are trying to stimulate me to focus on.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.05,0:09:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.15,0:09:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if I'm not sure what you're wanting me to focus on, then I'm not happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.30,0:09:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I applying myself to what you want me to focus on?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.62,0:09:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.54,0:09:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'm happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.84,0:09:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, sweetheart.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.18,0:09:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, gee, that was an easy one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.08,0:09:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people are hard to hire.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.20,0:09:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You're an easy one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.62,0:10:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,When we become judgmental, do we judge people for who they are, or do we judge people for what they are?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.95,0:10:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we do both.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.19,0:10:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We do both.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.90,0:10:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind really doesn't choose either or.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.83,0:10:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It spontaneously does them all at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.47,0:10:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The person is famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.25,0:10:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,They should be famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.89,0:10:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We're glad they're famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.39,0:10:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We're glad they're famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.51,0:10:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We're glad they're famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.55,0:10:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes we criticize somebody because they're famous for what we consider to be the wrong reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.42,0:10:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They've committed a crime or done something hideous, and so we're critical of them for being famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.82,0:10:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They're really not famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.30,0:10:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They're really infamous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.60,0:10:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Infamous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.56,0:10:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when fame reaches the height of negativity, we call it infamous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.72,0:10:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Infamous rather than famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.64,0:11:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,People, you know, serial killers and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.66,0:11:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't say they're famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.14,0:11:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We say they're infamous.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.72,0:11:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think that people sometimes set goals for themselves a little high?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.05,0:11:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, you know, sometimes people have higher expectations than they're willing to.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.68,0:11:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.48,0:11:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I think you can set the goal as high as you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.77,0:11:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And the expectations...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.53,0:11:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Expectation has to be then tailored to what's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.52,0:11:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you can set your goal to be President of the United States,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.74,0:11:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,but only one person is going to achieve that every four years.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.24,0:11:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So, there's nothing wrong with setting it as a goal and hoping to be the best.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.04,0:11:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope that we speak in a clearly eloquent and hopeful style this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.52,0:11:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.16,0:11:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And I would like to...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.36,0:12:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope that we've achieved that goal, that we've been able to help clarify
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.94,0:12:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that's an important part of human life.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.78,0:12:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Because we don't like to admit that it's a big part, but frankly, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.28,0:12:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Frankly, it's a big part, whether you have friends that like you
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.78,0:12:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're well thought of in your neighborhood
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.30,0:12:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're successful at whatever your work is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.36,0:12:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Those things are important.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.20,0:12:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd like to pretend they're not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.54,0:12:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But even if it's shoveling the sidewalk,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.50,0:12:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,when you get through shoveling all the snow off the sidewalk,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.46,0:12:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,you stand back and you look at it, you feel pleased.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.91,0:12:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I guess just feeling pleased and satisfied is sufficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.97,0:12:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just shovel all the snow off, nobody slipped and hurt themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.04,0:12:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and you feel good that you've fulfilled your responsibility as a good neighbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.30,0:12:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, true success is on different levels, then, actually.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.75,0:13:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you have your personal success, such as chopping the tree up
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.89,0:13:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and getting it done by 4 o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.21,0:13:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You have your financial success, which is the goals you set for yourself outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.97,0:13:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You have your spiritual success, which is your relationship with God.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.09,0:13:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you have, you know, family and everything else that are other successes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.37,0:13:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.53,0:13:27.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.65,0:13:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.21,0:13:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,A good wife, a good husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.75,0:13:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So, actually, success, when we lump it together, that's unfair
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.61,0:13:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,because there's so many different types of success.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.81,0:13:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, personal success, marital success, parental success.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.74,0:13:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,When your kid gets a good mark at school and comes home with a thing on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.46,0:13:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember when I was a kid, if you got good marks, you got a little star on your collar.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.48,0:13:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I couldn't wait to get home and show my mom my star on my collar.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.66,0:14:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,She said, what have you got there?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.14,0:14:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, star, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.82,0:14:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, boy, oh, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.54,0:14:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you tell me about a teacher you once had that you were telling...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.56,0:14:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You were very intellectual anyway, but you came home and told a story about something.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.60,0:14:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot what it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.52,0:14:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,A steamship or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.46,0:14:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And the teacher told your parents you had a very imaginative imagination, and here it was all true.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.08,0:14:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I was born with a genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.42,0:14:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I was often smarter than the teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.50,0:14:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And the teacher would give a short lecture on something,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.89,0:14:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I would correct the teacher because I didn't understand the subtleties of such things.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.87,0:14:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the teacher would explain their understanding, but I, as I said, had a genius IQ.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.23,0:15:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And I knew the whole encyclopedia.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.71,0:15:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I would elaborate on it for the teacher's benefit and the class's benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.93,0:15:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't do it for my benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.15,0:15:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought they'd like to know the facts, which I had read the encyclopedia already about.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.68,0:15:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was a kid, I read the encyclopedia.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.02,0:15:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Other kids are reading the funny papers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.23,0:15:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems very funny now that I was reading the encyclopedia.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.13,0:15:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember I got up to R, and I thought, oh, whammo, I'm up to R already, you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.78,0:15:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I've only been at it a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.34,0:15:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,A week?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.16,0:15:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.88,0:15:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It took you a week to read things?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.56,0:15:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,To get up to R, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.22,0:15:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my gosh.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.58,0:15:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that would be a success in itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.66,0:15:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if I finished X, Y, and Z in the meantime.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.06,0:15:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Zebra, Zappo.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.72,0:16:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,But, I mean, those are successes in their own right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.62,0:16:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.38,0:16:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.70,0:16:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I was just...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.90,0:16:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, it's successes to fulfill your own goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.34,0:16:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.84,0:16:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I was one time digging a ditch, and I set myself as a goal to dig six feet a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.80,0:16:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, six feet a ditch depends on how deep it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.77,0:16:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be quite a chore.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.15,0:16:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be shallow, it's not much.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.95,0:16:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But if it's deep, six feet a day is a lot of digging.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.97,0:16:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can remember when I dug six feet a day of ditch, and I said, wow, that was a great day, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.53,0:16:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.15,0:16:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,All stone and rock, and six feet of it was quite an accomplishment, especially when you were a small ectomorph like I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.29,0:16:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you were to...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.31,0:16:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I was an ectomorph.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.73,0:16:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.57,0:16:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what an ectomorph is?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.83,0:16:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.41,0:16:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, well, I was a small ectomorph.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.26,0:16:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I started digging a six-foot ditch was quite an accomplishment.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.64,0:17:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you were to tell people what type of goals they should set for themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.12,0:17:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,as far as it goes, as spiritual goals, what would you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.82,0:17:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to divide them up?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.36,0:17:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I was going to divide them up myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.34,0:17:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.82,0:17:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll say, all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.20,0:17:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.52,0:17:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I'll do it your way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.20,0:17:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.22,0:17:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual goals, you know, would be different for every person, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.52,0:17:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people would only consider becoming enlightened itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.87,0:17:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the fulfillment.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.77,0:17:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Other people, they just believe in God in the first place, or to even go to church.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.42,0:17:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I know people who never even go to church.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.79,0:17:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally on, what do you want to call it, day?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.05,0:17:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Ash Wednesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.83,0:17:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Ash Wednesday, they went to church.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.41,0:18:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that was an achievement for them, to just go to church and to fulfill the goal of,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.74,0:18:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,at least the external appearances of...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.84,0:18:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Religion, religiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.42,0:18:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We went to church on...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.27,0:18:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Ash Wednesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.15,0:18:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Ash Wednesday, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.57,0:18:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the name itself seemed mysterious, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.53,0:18:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Ash, what do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.80,0:18:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ashes to ashes and dust to dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.00,0:18:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.08,0:18:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you know, you can contemplate on that for a couple of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.44,0:18:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Ashes to ashes and dust to dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.56,0:18:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that fully signify?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.92,0:18:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the intellect has a quick answer for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.09,0:18:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But as you begin to contemplate, ashes to ashes and dust to dust,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.64,0:19:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I look at you and I say, you and I are both going to become ashes someday, sweetheart.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.04,0:19:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, honey, you never saw a U-Haul following a hearse, have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.24,0:19:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's a funny one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.46,0:19:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Very funny one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.30,0:19:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can't take it with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.50,0:19:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't take it with you, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.06,0:19:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you don't want to take it with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.69,0:19:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be excess baggage in heaven, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.26,0:19:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And heaven is more of a state of being rather than a state of doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.50,0:19:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.36,0:19:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,People say, what do you do in heaven?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.90,0:20:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there's nothing to do except just be.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.11,0:20:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So just being is enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.67,0:20:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,To do.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.86,0:20:13.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We went to church for some really Sunday there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.87,0:20:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And it wasn't, it had nothing to do with what was being done.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.72,0:20:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It was all the who of and the significance of the presence and the symbolism of it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.70,0:20:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The symbolism of reverence for the presence of God as existence is,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.82,0:20:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.88,0:20:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.20,0:20:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,done at this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.96,0:20:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And the hands are doing it of themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.16,0:20:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And I look at the hands and I say,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.72,0:20:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,hands, what are you expressing?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.65,0:20:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not expressing what I'm thinking because I'm not thinking anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.12,0:21:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I ask the hands to express the reverence of the presence of,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.98,0:21:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the awareness of the presence of God as existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.15,0:21:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thank the hands for fulfilling that obligation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.00,0:21:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So with the mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.44,0:21:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.76,0:21:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,it thinks the mind can then represent and therefore with a certain level of intention,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.24,0:21:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,every moment is expressing the presence of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.76,0:21:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The divinity of the presence of God is expressing itself every second.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.99,0:21:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.51,0:21:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,it cannot be otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.09,0:21:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It can only be the failure,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.53,0:21:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the ability to recognize it as such or the inability to recognize it as such.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.76,0:21:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So as you and I sit here and speak,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.74,0:21:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I say,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.00,0:22:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel by using whatever talents I may have in the service of,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.14,0:22:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.26,0:22:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that I'm serving God by sitting here next to you and you're doing the same thing
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.62,0:22:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.58,0:22:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So you and I right now are serving God to the best of our knowledge to share our
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.51,0:22:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding of divinity and the intention of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.47,0:22:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and how to fulfill that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.08,0:22:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That may not be somebody else's,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.06,0:22:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but it doesn't make any difference
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.30,0:22:36.67,Default,,0,0,0,,because I want to hear everybody's idea on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.93,0:22:38.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to hear everybody's thoughts
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.67,0:22:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,on how do I fulfill God's obligation
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.31,0:22:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,or my responsibility to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.78,0:22:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that's a really interesting question
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.68,0:22:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to ask everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.91,0:22:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to ask a whole dozen different people
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.59,0:22:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,doing different things in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.01,0:22:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you feel you're fulfilling God's obligation
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.71,0:23:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and get the interesting answers?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.66,0:23:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I go to work every day and I support my children
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.22,0:23:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and I pay my taxes and I'm good to my wife
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.70,0:23:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and I shovel the snow
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.24,0:23:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and I make sure the car has gas in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.06,0:23:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Fulfilling one's obligation to human life
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.50,0:23:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is a way of fulfilling the intention of divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.92,0:23:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,because it is through divinity
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.91,0:23:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that we experience life.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.77,0:23:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And at least it's human form.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.82,0:23:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of people think that success
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.12,0:23:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is actually changing the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.20,0:23:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,making a difference in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.00,0:23:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That's worldly success, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.02,0:23:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, yeah, but a lot of people set their goals at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.00,0:23:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.98,0:23:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They want to change the thought
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.10,0:23:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of everyone around them.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.64,0:23:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.40,0:23:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,To make a difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.66,0:23:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Influence.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.80,0:23:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, they want to put their mark
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.70,0:23:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,on the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.76,0:24:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you're saying is
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.70,0:24:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,by being a better person spiritually,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.98,0:24:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you do put your mark on the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.12,0:24:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We do it silently.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.56,0:24:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But we do it silently.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.94,0:24:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.56,0:24:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that you're present in the room
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.16,0:24:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,makes what goes on in the room differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.85,0:24:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.55,0:24:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me have your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.14,0:24:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you say nothing,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.54,0:24:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the presence of a...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.38,0:24:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritually advanced person in a room
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.22,0:24:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,changes everything that happens in that room.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.90,0:24:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.42,0:24:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.28,0:24:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So even if you just lay on the floor
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.14,0:24:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and say nothing,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.52,0:24:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy that you emanate
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.55,0:24:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is affecting everything around you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.70,0:24:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's a nice thing to know,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.12,0:24:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're light.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.84,0:24:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, your life has value
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.84,0:24:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,all the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.42,0:24:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,even though you're not out there
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.76,0:24:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,doing spectacular things,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.38,0:24:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,being famous, writing famous music,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.22,0:24:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,appearing on stage,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.52,0:25:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,or just...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.64,0:25:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so let's have the arm again.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.86,0:25:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Just being the excellence
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.67,0:25:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,of the possibility within yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.31,0:25:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of whatever it may be
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.63,0:25:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is serving God.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.55,0:25:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, to sing the best song you can sing,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.71,0:25:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to dance the best dance,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.26,0:25:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you and I right now
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.48,0:25:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,are fulfilling an obligation to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.10,0:25:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You said we're going to be giving
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.72,0:25:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,a little talk this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.24,0:25:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that we're going to be recording,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.32,0:25:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.68,0:25:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I was panic-stricken.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.90,0:25:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, oh, my God,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.92,0:25:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't thought about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.12,0:25:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What am I going to talk about?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.42,0:25:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we sat down here,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.14,0:25:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,my inner mind said,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.24,0:25:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, my God,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.84,0:25:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,what are we going to talk about?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.95,0:25:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And right now, my mind is saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.61,0:25:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, my God,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.53,0:25:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,what are we going to talk about?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.75,0:25:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no idea
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.74,0:25:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,what we're going to be speaking about
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.20,0:25:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.48,0:25:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me have your arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.26,0:25:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.14,0:25:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted you to give me my arm
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.48,0:26:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,for no reason this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.48,0:26:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.46,0:26:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.58,0:26:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's important to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.10,0:26:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I already asked you before.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.96,0:26:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought if it was not God's intention
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.06,0:26:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,for me to be sitting here
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.30,0:26:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,speaking to you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.28,0:26:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,in the style in which I am,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.40,0:26:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no other possibility
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.30,0:26:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,except to be doing
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.31,0:26:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,what God wants me to do,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.75,0:26:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,which is sitting here
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.55,0:26:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,commenting to you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.01,0:26:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,on your presence
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.45,0:26:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and the effect that it has on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.89,0:26:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So you, as yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.60,0:26:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,what would you say
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.14,0:26:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What would you say success looks like to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.23,0:26:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,To me?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.23,0:26:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.23,0:26:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.23,0:26:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you share that with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.19,0:26:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, to me, success means multiple things simultaneously, because you might ask it from
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.31,0:26:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,different areas.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.11,0:27:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I being successful in fulfilling your expectation of me this morning to come forth and spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.06,0:27:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,answer these questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.87,0:27:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I'm doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.87,0:27:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm happy that I am fulfilling what I understood was your question to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.55,0:27:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Could we go into the studio and discuss a few of these important questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.15,0:27:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So I feel satisfied that I am fulfilling your expectation of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.80,0:27:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I'm hoping that my doing so makes you happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.20,0:27:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So your happiness is part of my intention all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.80,0:27:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I always want you to be happy, and there's no moment when I ... I've never had
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.08,0:27:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a wish that you should not be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.92,0:27:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Never.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.92,0:27:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I never crossed my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.91,0:27:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to be happy all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.97,0:28:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the only reason I'm worried about how the doggies are behaving is I want the doggies
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.99,0:28:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,to add to your happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.99,0:28:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want the doggie to have an accident, which would detract from your happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.02,0:28:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why we let the doggie out, to make sure that the doggie wouldn't interrupt our
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.75,0:28:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,fulfillment of this obligation this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.09,0:28:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the search for enlightenment or bettering one's spiritual understanding, is that ... it's
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.69,0:28:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,an entirely different success than, say, worldly success?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.69,0:28:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, yes, spiritually, success has nothing to do with the world, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.65,0:28:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,On one level, it has everything to do with it, but on the level at which you're asking
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.93,0:28:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,it, it has really nothing to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.15,0:29:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Because success is an inner goal, an inner expectation, partly based on an awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.99,0:29:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of what your capacities are.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.48,0:29:22.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So if I feel I've successfully, adequately answered your questions, then I'll feel satisfied
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.47,0:29:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,that I've adequately addressed them, carefully listened to them, and allowed themselves to
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.14,0:29:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,spontaneously answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.56,0:29:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So these moments that we have right this very instant are all happening spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.84,0:29:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no idea of what they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.34,0:29:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.53,0:29:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what to talk about, other than that we were going to be here to speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.51,0:29:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So I trust, there's a certain trust, there's a certain inner trust that my inner self will
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.20,0:30:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically adjust itself to fulfill the expectations of the moment, one of them being
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.58,0:30:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that your satisfaction at the way in which I'm answering you right this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.55,0:30:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm feeling happy that you ... you might possibly be happy with the way I'm answering
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.57,0:30:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you right this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.57,0:30:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm feeling happy that you ... you might possibly be happy with the way I'm answering
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.57,0:30:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you right this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.57,0:30:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You might be happy with the way I'm being right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.57,0:30:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you being happy with the way I'm being right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.51,0:30:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.51,0:30:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.51,0:30:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.75,0:30:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.67,0:30:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not just saying that to make me feel good.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.81,0:30:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.41,0:30:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's another ... you have to put a point down.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.07,0:30:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.07,0:30:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So a lot of people that are successful in their spiritual life do not have worldly success.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.25,0:30:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, that's ...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.25,0:30:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.25,0:30:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You know.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.25,0:30:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Because ... do you think it's because they concentrated all their ... I mean that the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.44,0:30:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual success is more important to them than worldly?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.72,0:30:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.08,0:30:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And the fulfillment is of spiritual goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.76,0:30:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The other day we went to church for, what is it,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.48,0:30:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Happy Wednesday morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.02,0:30:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you call it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.90,0:31:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Ash Wednesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.02,0:31:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.44,0:31:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Ash Wednesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.10,0:31:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Ash Wednesday, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.22,0:31:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Unhappy day.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.82,0:31:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we got there on time,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.94,0:31:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,fulfilled the obligation to ourself
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.14,0:31:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that we decided we wished to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.26,0:31:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Not everybody goes, and we didn't always go every year.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.26,0:31:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Some years you feel like for some reason
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.84,0:31:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it's important that we go this week.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.30,0:31:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be for unknown reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.59,0:31:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I think most things happen for unknown reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.05,0:31:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I think our mind gives us an explanation,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.39,0:31:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,but I think the explanation may have very little to do
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.23,0:31:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,with the reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.65,0:31:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,There was possibly people affected just by our physical presence
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.31,0:31:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,in the room itself, of which we had no comprehension.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.35,0:32:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,A little doggy barking by the side of the beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.68,0:32:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't know he's barking to make you happy,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.84,0:32:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,but that may be what keeps a little sick kid alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.98,0:32:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The puppy that loves the sick child keeps the child alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.59,0:32:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The sick puppy doesn't know it's doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.37,0:32:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the puppy doesn't know it's doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.34,0:32:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are children in hospitals whose lives are extended
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.58,0:32:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,by the presence of having a puppy or a dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.88,0:32:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think the study of the effect of dogs on human life
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.22,0:32:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,is very, very fascinating.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.21,0:32:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only that it extends your life ten years,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.61,0:32:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,but it increases the quality.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.98,0:32:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So the quality of our life is much higher
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.54,0:32:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,since we got Kelsey dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.49,0:32:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't know what Kelsey cost us, five bucks?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.93,0:32:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.41,0:32:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.91,0:32:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.41,0:32:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Three?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.91,0:32:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.41,0:32:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Fifteen?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.91,0:32:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We adopted her, so no, it wasn't that.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.91,0:32:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,No?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.41,0:32:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.91,0:33:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the presence of that dog in our life makes a difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.30,0:33:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And even now as we speak, in the back of my mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.80,0:33:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I realize the dog is sitting home waiting for us to come home
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.80,0:33:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,from the studio.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.80,0:33:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And that as we get closer and closer, her tail will start to wag.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.80,0:33:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,She will feel happier and happier and more and more excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.80,0:33:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.80,0:33:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That makes life joyful.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.80,0:33:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that your existence brings joy to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.99,0:33:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I approach the kitties, they start to purr.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.31,0:33:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The big orange kitty always goes purr, purr, purr, purr.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.31,0:33:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And that makes me happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.31,0:33:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I can hear the kitties' happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.31,0:33:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And the doggie's tail is wagging.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.31,0:33:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we've got an African talking parrot.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.31,0:33:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that his name? African talking parrot?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.31,0:33:47.31,Default,,0,0,0,,African gray.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.31,0:33:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,African gray.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.31,0:33:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And the parrot starts talking up a storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.31,0:33:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So the kitty's purring.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.31,0:33:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The dog's tail is wagging.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.31,0:34:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And the African gray parrot is talking up a big storm there.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.31,0:34:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called a zoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.31,0:34:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,All of that adds to the joy of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.31,0:34:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.31,0:34:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.53,0:34:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,A joie de vivre.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.53,0:34:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I like that word, joie de vivre.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.53,0:34:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Joie de vivre.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.53,0:34:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Joie, joie de vivre.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.53,0:34:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.53,0:34:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you would say is, I mean, it's kind of common knowledge that a spiritual aspirant a lot of times is not as successful in the world as other people because that just seems to be secondary to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.56,0:34:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's pretty true.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.56,0:34:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,A secondary goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.56,0:34:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay to have money, but it's considered a detriment.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.56,0:34:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.56,0:34:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.56,0:34:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.78,0:34:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Enough to have, you know, your needs fulfilled.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.78,0:34:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, that's all you really need.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.78,0:34:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And the rest is irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.94,0:34:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.94,0:35:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got a new pair of shoes on.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.71,0:35:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm proud of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.71,0:35:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever I see my...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.71,0:35:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you see new shoes?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.71,0:35:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.71,0:35:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, those are new shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.71,0:35:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm very proud of these new shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.71,0:35:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I haven't had a new pair of shoes in, I don't know, years.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.71,0:35:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to me, a new pair of shoes is a big, exciting event.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.71,0:35:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.71,0:35:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.71,0:35:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So now I have to break them in.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.71,0:35:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I've decided that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.71,0:35:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The upside is you have a new pair of shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.71,0:35:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The downside is you have to break it in.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.71,0:35:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.71,0:35:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I think everybody should enjoy these brand new shoes, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.71,0:35:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But it couldn't get simpler, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.71,0:35:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So, success is a name that we put on an act that, whether it's a new business or a new
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.71,0:35:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,business, it's a new business.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.71,0:35:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a new business.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.71,0:35:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a new business.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.71,0:35:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a new business.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.71,0:35:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a new business.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.71,0:35:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a new business.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.71,0:35:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a new business.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.35,0:35:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a new business.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.48,0:35:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I mean, we're, it's, and actually, the more important success is the personal success
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.45,0:35:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than the worldly.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.95,0:35:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.95,0:35:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, to certain people that would be.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.81,0:36:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, other people, worldly success is what they would.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.07,0:36:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It is worldly, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.57,0:36:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't divide the two.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.57,0:36:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.57,0:36:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to some people, they want the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.04,0:36:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,To achieve worldly success.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.76,0:36:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for instance, what I'm trying to do right now is answer your question.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.64,0:36:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.76,0:36:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,questions to the best of my capability.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.40,0:36:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What the world thinks of it is rather irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.26,0:36:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, wasn't it Carnegie, who's a big steel manufacturer, and he was very successful
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.52,0:36:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and had all this money, and he gave all of it away at the end of his life?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.10,0:36:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything that he had accomplished his whole life, he gave away.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.02,0:36:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I think that's a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.86,0:36:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What else are you going to do with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.94,0:36:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't take it with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.94,0:36:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what he did is he created these museums and...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.18,0:36:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.18,0:36:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I see what you're saying, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.64,0:36:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So that other people could enjoy...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.70,0:36:55.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.70,0:36:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.70,0:36:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.70,0:36:58.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.70,0:36:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it was Carnegie.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.70,0:37:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're trying to do is share your success with the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.59,0:37:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that we have people who are interested in listening to us speak with each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.87,0:37:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the fact that that is so makes our life successful, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.98,0:37:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.98,0:37:19.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.78,0:37:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.78,0:37:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But I mean, I know wealthy people, and that would be the last thing they would do, is
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.17,0:37:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to give everything, their whole life, you know, they wouldn't want to give it all away.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.11,0:37:32.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you can't take it with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.59,0:37:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What would you do with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.59,0:37:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, but I mean, there's lots of people that pass it along or whatever, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.61,0:37:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to the next generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.61,0:37:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, oh, I see what you mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.59,0:37:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.59,0:37:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Control of their wealth.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.59,0:37:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.59,0:37:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Control of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.59,0:37:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.59,0:37:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Control of it, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.59,0:37:48.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.55,0:37:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, that's just, you know, people don't have to be ashamed of normal human emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.74,0:38:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Normal human emotions is to crave success, recognition, worldly goods, comfort.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.75,0:38:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are just normal for the human.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.27,0:38:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think a person should feel guilty about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.48,0:38:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I hope people enjoy our discussion right now, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.36,0:38:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that selfish, or is it just the goodwill, or it's just the fact that I care about people
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.62,0:38:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and their happiness?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.25,0:38:30.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I want them to enjoy the moment, and that what we're speaking about with each other
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.15,0:38:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,stimulates a similar positive response within them, so I'm not just talking to you so that
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.41,0:38:43.03,Default,,0,0,0,,we can play this back and enjoy ourselves talking to each other, because I've already
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.03,0:38:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,heard what we had to say, you know, but what you want to do is share your enjoyment.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.94,0:38:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the same as if you play piano or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.96,0:38:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.48,0:38:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there was a great pianist, pretty well-known pianist, and in fact, we had two, we owned
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.02,0:39:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,two pianos in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.87,0:39:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody in the house played piano, and everybody played it to the best of their ability, so
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.31,0:39:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,we enjoyed each other's capacity and capabilities as a pianist, and then I took up the violin
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.42,0:39:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.42,0:39:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Plus, I was also a singer.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.77,0:39:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.77,0:39:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I was also a well-known boy soprano, and so I had this incredible singing voice, plus
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.78,0:39:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I could play the violin, plus I could play the piano, so, and then I enjoyed music, and
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.72,0:39:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I still do listen to a great orchestra, so the enjoyment of music and all of its expressions
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.52,0:39:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,adds to the joy of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.24,0:39:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.24,0:39:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, on the way home, if we had to go home, we'd go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.24,0:39:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If we had a little music in the electric cart that we're going to go home in, I'd probably
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.36,0:40:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,play the music to add to the celebration of this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.49,0:40:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.19,0:40:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.25,0:40:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.20,0:40:17.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So—
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.56,0:40:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I just got the name of that song.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.58,0:40:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Merrily, we rolled along.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.60,0:40:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.60,0:40:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.44,0:40:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's it's a choice that we have to make whether we want a spirit whether we
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.72,0:40:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,consider spiritual success more important to us or we consider financial
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.16,0:40:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,success yeah yeah whether we're going to divide them up that way and classify
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.50,0:40:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,them is that way right because you can be financially successful and also
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.42,0:40:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritually right they don't preclude each other right and you can be rich as
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.46,0:41:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,all get out and not pious or you can be very pious and very poor it's better to
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.46,0:41:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,be rich and pious it's better to go home from church in a Cadillac than peddling
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.15,0:41:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself in a rusty old bicycle a modicum of it so all these things come
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.21,0:41:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,down to balance right you know religiosity you can also become a
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.50,0:41:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,religious nut you know
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.04,0:41:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,religious nut you know
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.14,0:41:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,religious nut you know
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.16,0:41:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,pain in the neck so all these things is a matter of balance how much time you
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.29,0:41:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and I spend with each other talking and laughing with each other how much time
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.63,0:41:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,we spend with our doggy and playing with her dog so it seems to me that
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.17,0:41:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,everything we do is a matter of balance there's a bad matter of balance of
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.59,0:42:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,affection of playfulness of rest of sleep of work of wash their
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.01,0:42:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in the car when it needs being washed so life is a is a constant uh fluctuating diversity
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.27,0:42:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,over which we have no control whether it rains today or it doesn't so if if one could
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.81,0:42:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,balance their life between their spiritual goals and their successful goals then you could have
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.70,0:42:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,both you can certainly have both and certainly being spiritual is part of my idea is successful
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.55,0:42:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh other people might consider it only you know financial successes at this so it would be
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.82,0:42:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the self-fulfillment of our own comprehension and understanding which is our level of maturity
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.40,0:42:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course how old you are uh-huh and you mean at 92 you're going to be more interested
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.66,0:43:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,in whether heaven's a reality or not than at 18 right
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.18,0:43:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.24,0:43:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,i guess yeah you're right so as well i think it's the hindus that that um they they you know
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.72,0:43:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,give up everything at the end of their life and and devote everything to god or i don't know it's
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.14,0:43:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,just restricted anybody i i thought everybody did that sort of well yes i mean material things get
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.20,0:43:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,rid of things well i don't know if it's material but they what they do do is they do do a lot of
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.30,0:43:41.94,Default,,0,0,0,,it's they devote the last part of their life to god oh okay yeah so if we all would take those
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.94,0:43:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,lessons and devote um you know the first part of your life it's you know you're young and then you
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.10,0:43:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,have babies and then you have you know then you go into the to the later part of your life and as
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.16,0:44:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you reach the later part of your life you realize that you're you're spiritual um because it becomes
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.90,0:44:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,more important oh yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.56,0:44:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,so it would be nice if we could balance that throughout our life rather than just
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.20,0:44:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,expecting that to happen at the end yes well i think people are brought up properly uh that
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.26,0:44:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that does happen okay you know as a kid you go to sunday school and uh while your folks are in
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.18,0:44:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,church you're at sunday school and then as you get older then finally you get married when you
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.97,0:44:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,do that you do that with the priest and the church
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.93,0:44:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh it doesn't mean that it's wrong to be non-spiritual or not materialistic i mean to be
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.64,0:44:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,materialistic it's not wrong uh that people are not spiritually interested i feel that's just not
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.71,0:45:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,an area of their life that karmically is important at this moment it might be in fact quite the
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.47,0:45:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,opposite you know quit up put all that praying and get the car washed
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.92,0:45:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,okay
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.24,0:45:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,let's have let's praying a little more work around here
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.48,0:45:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,if you prayed all day instead of cook that have complaints before you know what all right
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.76,0:45:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,don't we ever eat around this joint everybody not yet i come on you think
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.30,0:45:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,we're just busy praying
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.42,0:45:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,i'll have to try that
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.22,0:45:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,i'm gonna try that see how that works
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.64,0:45:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,when you tell me today we're gonna pray a little more work around here
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.44,0:45:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,having meatloaf. Isn't that right? Okay, so yeah that'd be something I'd sit down at
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.15,0:45:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,dinner and she says, I didn't get the dinner done. And I'd say, why do you? Because I was
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.33,0:46:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,praying we didn't get the meatloaf cooked. Then I'd feel guilty, see, that I'm mad
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.66,0:46:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that you, you know, that I want my meatloaf instead of having you pray. So
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.38,0:46:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that would make me feel materialistic and greedy, that I'm concerned about my
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.33,0:46:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,eating instead of her praying. I should be concerned about whether she prays
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.87,0:46:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,not whether I eat meatloaf or not. You know, it's funny how human feeling can be so
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.23,0:46:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,intricate and circuitous in many ways, seemingly ambivalent, ambiguous, rather.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.09,0:46:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So would you say that success is
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.41,0:46:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,a
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.45,0:46:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,just a term that we put on a act or a, how do I want to say, I'm trying to think how to say this,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.25,0:47:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,success is a word that we put to an action. Or an achievement. Or achievement. Or a state of being.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.66,0:47:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Or a state of being. Worldly or spiritual or intellectual, it could apply to any.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.58,0:47:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Intellectually you get straight A in school, you did well. Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.88,0:47:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to church with sincerity in your heart. That would be a fulfillment.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.91,0:47:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,But you brought up the fact that balance is very important between all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.91,0:47:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I think extremes otherwise make your prayer sort of quirky.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.91,0:47:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay to pray all day but somebody's got to shovel the sidewalk, you know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.55,0:47:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.07,0:47:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.37,0:47:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.69,0:47:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.93,0:47:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that's a good question.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.17,0:47:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.19,0:47:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
